    "At higher temperatures, thermal energy excites electrons, creating additional charge carriers that contribute to dark current.",
    "While more prominent in the absence of light, dark current also influences the electrical characteristics of the solar cell under illuminated conditions, potentially reducing overall efficiency (Markvart, 2022).",
